    - target: {fileID: 1899498462160688433, guid: 356912b0ad4fa8a4fbbd179f5ef9f089, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "A dissecting microscope is designed for low-magnification observation
        of specimens. It uses light reflected from the specimen\u2019s surface rather
        than transmitted light. The first simple microscope, consisting of a small,
        single high-powered converging lens for examining freshwater microorganisms,
        was invented by the Dutch scientist Antonie van Leeuwenhoek.\n"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
